text:
|| journey to recovery vol.1 ||
~
~
if you‚Äôve read my posts then your up to date with what is going on or know somewhat of the battles i‚Äôm fighting through daily.
~
today has been such a gloomy, rainy day. i‚Äôm a sucker for cool air and rain. it speaks to my soul in ways i cant put into words. i‚Äôm ocd badly to a point where i want my kids to be creative but hate messes. like ‚Äúlet me help you so it won‚Äôt be messy!‚Äù however it‚Äôs good to let them get messy and create using their imaginations.
however this new me that is starting to evolve, embraces messes. it started raining and i went outside and started jumping in those puddles that i dreaded my kids going in.
~
my old ways was still me but i think the me that has been hidden by fear, pain, trauma, hurt, rejection, betrayal, lost, not good enough, self doubt, self hatred, no hope, rape, wanting to end my life and almost succeeded, is coming out. embracing new adventures. this has been me along but the real me is evolving. living flexible and carefree. having an open mind to everything and anything!
~
friends who are fighting mental illness...it‚Äôs okay if all you did today was breathe!! that‚Äôs huge! make a promise to me that you will take time for you. take a second to do something that makes your inner soul happy. stand in the rain! jump in puddles. smile because you‚Äôre here and i‚Äôm glad you are!! ‚ù§Ô∏è
~
mamas, anyone....if your fighting demons... if your darkness is so dark and you don‚Äôt have the strength to fight anymore....message me! i‚Äôm here for you!! you have someone here that knows how dark it can be or could get. i‚Äôm here to listen. always!

friends who are fighting mental illness...it‚Äôs okay if all you did today was breathe!! that‚Äôs huge! make a promise to me that you will take time for you. take a second to do something that makes your inner soul happy. stand in the rain! jump in puddles. smile because you‚Äôre here and i‚Äôm glad you are!! ‚ù§Ô∏è
~
mamas, anyone....if your fighting demons... if your darkness is so dark and you don‚Äôt have the strength to fight anymore....message me! i‚Äôm here for you!! you have someone here that knows how dark it can be or could get. i‚Äôm here to listen. always!

#mehrrealit√§taufinstagram . hmm, ich versuche mich mal an ner liste.
üî∏Ô∏èmir brennt ab und zu mal das essen an, insbesondere wenn ich die linsensuppe im emailletopf aufw√§rme. das aktuelle malheur ist passiert, als ich gerade dabei war, ein foto f√ºr instagram zu machen. üòÇ
üî∏Ô∏èseit ich so viel auf smartphone oder computertastaturen tippe, ist meine ohnehin nicht so h√ºbsche handschrift exorbitant scheusslich geworden. üî∏Ô∏èich bin staturm√§√üig mehr so hummel als biene, geschweige denn wespe. zugleich tanze ich sehr gerne gesellschaftstanz und rege mich immer extrem auf, wenn ich an tanzpartner gerate, die der auffassung sind, dass st√§mmige frauen sich nicht bewegen k√∂nnen oder wollen, und √ºber ihre vorurteile dann jegliche form der etikette und h√∂flichkeit vergessen. manchmal verleiden mir solche erlebnisse dann auch den spa√ü am tanzen allgemein.
üî∏Ô∏èich bin genervt davon, wieviel in der welt abh√§ngig von vitamin b und selbstmarketing ist, wie wenig substanz manchmal z√§hlt, und finde, f√ºr menschen sollte es auch so tolle initiativen geben, wie f√ºr hutzeliges, nicht normgerechtes gem√ºse und obst. sowas wie @culinarymisfits oder

text: years ago, i entered into a legal battle. it was a coming of age story - a survivor reclaiming her power. when it started, my lawyers advised that i not write anything about it. not even in private. those types of things become evidence, i learned, and sometimes the emotional processing and asking that lands on paper might serve the soul, but makes a mess in legal settings. spoiler alert: the justice system is backwards. so there i was, a lifelong writer who hated my own voice and held a grudge against god for giving me the ability at all. a writer who, despite a stint in journalism and mild success in certain circles, walked away. i was already silent. i had stopped writing years before there was a case to protect. the requirement to put my pen down was the permission i so desperately craved. it was permission to deny myself and turn inward. when the case ended, i felt empowered and heard. i realized that, for far too long and by my own free will, i had thrown away my own words. i operated in a toxic bubble of self-doubt, embarrassment, zero self-worth and crippling shame. my return to my voice, my words, has been life giving. ironically, i don‚Äôt have the words for it. i am forever changed. if there is anything that i hope you hear, it‚Äôs this: please don‚Äôt abandoned your power. ask all of the questions. challenge others to consider new perspectives. speak up for yourself, and for others. don‚Äôt allow the bigger, intimidating players of society to convince you that your voice is too small or insignificant to be raised. it‚Äôs not. we need you. we need to hear you. don‚Äôt fear disagreement. don‚Äôt fear judgement. don‚Äôt fear your own voice. you have power in your throat. raise hell when you need to and bring forth peace as often as possible. there are people, institutions and rules that will try to silence you along the way. don‚Äôt help them. don‚Äôt join them. be bold in your statements, be courageous with your truth, be unapologetic in your curiosity. and when the hand of the person next to you isn‚Äôt seen, use your power to raise your voice in their direction. and hey, if you‚Äôve been quiet in your life, shame does not live here. i have your back. many of us do. üñ§

text:
trump and his people are awful!!!! ‚Äî‚Äî- the museum of african-american history and culture is in part a catalog of cruelty. amid all the stories of perseverance, tragedy, and unlikely triumph are the artifacts of inhumanity and barbarism: the child-size slave shackles, the bright red robes of the wizards of the ku klux klan, the recordings of civil-rights protesters being brutalized by police. the artifacts that persist in my memory, the way a bright flash does when you close your eyes, are the photographs of lynchings. but it‚Äôs not the burned, mutilated bodies that stick with me. it‚Äôs the faces of the white men in the crowd. there‚Äôs the photo of the lynching of thomas shipp and abram smith in indiana in 1930, in which a white man can be seen grinning at the camera as he tenderly holds the hand of his wife or girlfriend. there‚Äôs the undated photo from duluth, minnesota, in which grinning white men stand next to the mutilated, half-naked bodies of two men lashed to a post in the street‚Äîone of the white men is straining to get into the picture, his smile cutting from ear to ear. there‚Äôs the photo of a crowd of white men huddled behind the smoldering corpse of a man burned to death; one of them is wearing a smart suit, a fedora hat, and a bright smile.
 their names have mostly been lost to time. but these grinning men were someone‚Äôs brother, son, husband, father. they were human beings, people who took immense pleasure in the utter cruelty of torturing others to death‚Äîand were so proud of doing so that they posed for photographs with their handiwork, jostling to ensure they caught the eye of the lens, so that the world would know they‚Äôd been there. their cruelty made them feel good, it made them feel proud, it made them feel happy. and it made them feel closer to one another.

alas, #bernardobertolucci, who just passed away. he was celebrated throughout his career as a brilliant director, a ‚Äúa genius auteur,‚Äù a ‚Äúmaster.‚Äù his films were undeniably original, stunningly visualized and psychologically complex. i admire many of them. but he was also undeniably a male filmmaker of his generation ‚Äî exploitative of women actors, in particular maria schneider,
an early #metoo survivor and bravely vocal about her exploitation on the set of her first major film, which she said left her feeling ‚Äúa little raped.‚Äù and for which he said he had no regrets. he passed away at the same time as paris‚Äô huge #noustoutes interesectional feminist rally yesterday. i‚Äôve written about last tango in  paris elsewhere, for example on my blog who cares about actresses, which is dedicated to schneider. this is a drawing of schneider and bertolucci - a ‚Äútowering figure‚Äù - in a series of maria studies i did while researching her life - drawn from a film still of them on set in 1972.

text:
harrowing!! sometimes it's so hard to review a movie strictly based on the technicalities and analysing the perfection it is made with. especially, when it deals with a grim subject as this does and it only makes it even more appalling when you learn that it's based on some real life experience which someone had. it's only fitting this story comes out now, in the wake of the #metoo movement, where people are still bickering over the credibility of some of the claims. sometimes, we rely too much on the certitude and evidence of something, rather than evaluating the possibility of the actual truth, by bringing the integrity of the claimant. 
the movie, which is an actual memoir of the director, jennifer fox, tells us about the bitter experience - which she failed to apprehend as one, in a very coherent and unapologetic manner. it tells us how our memories try to conciliate with something which is so frightening and vulnerable in order to keep us going forward, only to leave the scars behind and the wounds wide open. the cast did a perfect job. elizabeth debicki and jason ritter were wonderful at portraying their complex, thankless characters. isabelle n√©lisse, sister of the talented sophie n√©lisse, was so impressive along with laura dern and ellen burstyn. this was truly an oscar worthy performance from laura dern, to portray the entanglements of her character while making the audiences feel what "jenny" is going through or what she went through. this movie and the topic it deals with, is something we have to put a lot of thoughts on. 
@thetalemovie @hbo @isabelle_nelisse @jason_ritter @lauradern

text: obituary: days after the death of #celebritymom #kimporter media mogul announced her own mother has died. vernita and #oprah had a longtime rift because @oprah says she was raped and  became #pregnant at age 14. she gave up the baby for #adoption her mother had also given up a child - #oprah sister patricia, who later tracked down her family information and sold her harrowing story to the tabloids. oprah spoke on that saying: ‚Äúfor the first time, i realized that that was a gift to me. pat going to the tabloids and telling the story about my having the baby was a gift because it released me from the shame that my mother still carries today [for giving up pat]. i thought, had she not done that, i would still be exactly where my mother is‚Äîstuck in the shame.‚Äù addressing her mother during a televised reunion with patricia, winfrey added, ‚Äúyou can let that go. you can let the shame go. there are millions of people all over this country who are just like you, who have given up their children because they knew at the time that they could not provide the best for them. so, vernita, you can let that go.‚Äù #blacktwitter #blackmoms #metoo #sexualabuse  source: essence magazine read: https://www.essence.com/amp/celebrity/what-oprah-learned-from-her-mother-quote/

text:
two women, a mother and her daughter, pray at the grave of a family member who was murdered by her boyfriend. 
despite a 2012 law which raised the maximum prison sentence for ‚Äúfemicide,‚Äù the killing of a woman or girl on account of her gender, argentina is still struggling against widespread gender-based violence. thankfully, a grassroots, women-led movement known as ni una menos (not one [woman] less) has arisen in argentina, and is working to empower women and defend their human rights. in this series, karl mancini (@karlitomancini) shares some of his work on the inspiring women of ni una menos and their fight for justice. to learn more about both mancini's work and ni una menos, please follow the link in our bio. 
#opensociety #argentina #niunamenos #femicide #femicidio #conmisderechosnotemetas #16days #genderbasedviolence #metoo #hearmetoo

text:
#untothewhirlwind is here to share love, insight and bring up every concept people ignore, reject and refuse to discuss. #mentalhealth & #wellness 
i share my problems. i determine a habit or a possible solution. 
i try to incorporate new things into my life to enrich the experience.
the very same thing is extended to my #audience.
here, i will never shy away from lifting someone's spirits up!
because, i too know what you mean, or how you feel or felt those same feelings- at one point and time... possibly or maybe not.

‚Ñπto me, there seems to be many emotions many people have never felt before and there are so many we can experience at any moment based off life changing in an instant. 
alls im saying is this ig platform is here to offer #positivity & #optimism to the masses!

text:
if you think you might be experiencing domestic violence, there are things you can do: .
.
.
-	you are not alone. reach out ‚Äì speak to someone you trust or get in touch with a specialist who can offer you help and support. -	it is not your fault ‚Äì abuse is a choice your partner makes and only he is responsible. that is how he shows who he is. -	domestic violence is a crime therefore illegal. you can free yourself from violence. contact the police authorities in your area. -	contact 061 681 66 33, stiftung frauenhaus beider basel. .
.

text:
r.i.p .
.
"i left the ending ambiguous, because that is the way life is." .
.
~  bernardo bertolucci

p.s ~ curtains

bernardo bertolucci, who¬†died on monday at the age of 77, has received widespread acclaim for  #filmmaking, winning #oscars, #goldenglobes, and the¬†first-ever honorary palme d‚Äôor award¬†at the #cannesfilmfestival in 2011

but one part of his career has been the subject of increasing scrutiny in recent years: a #rape scene in bertolucci‚Äôs 1972 film¬†last tango in paris. marlon brando‚Äôs character, paul, rapes actress maria schneider‚Äôs character, jeanne, using a stick of butter as lubricant. in a¬†2007 interview¬†with the daily mail, schneider said the scene wasn‚Äôt in the original script, and that brando and bertolucci had told her about it just before they began filming.

the scene is intended to be #violent and disturbing with paul hitting jeanne and penetrating her as she cries. but as schneider made clear the feelings of #violation we see onscreen aren‚Äôt just acting ‚Äî they‚Äôre real. ‚Äúi was so angry,‚Äù she said. ‚Äúi felt humiliated and to be honest, i felt a little #raped both by marlon and by bertolucci.‚Äù the scene became the target of renewed scrutiny¬†beginning in 2016, when a 2013 video clip in which bertolucci discussed the film went viral. the director acknowledged that he‚Äôd sprung the butter detail on schneider at the last minute, because he wanted her onscreen humiliation and rage to be real. ‚Äúi wanted maria to feel, not to act,‚Äù he said.

brando didn‚Äôt actually penetrate schneider in the scene. but it was an incident of real sexual humiliation nonetheless, by all accounts. and in a time of reckoning around sexual misconduct, misogyny, and abuse of power in hollywood, it deserves to be remembered as part of his legacy.

bertolucci argued that it was necessary to humiliate schneider in order to make his #film. but that argument reveals a fundamental #inequity that the¬†#metoo movement¬†is only beginning to expose: in #hollywood, some people, most of them men, have the power to decide what makes great #art ‚Äî and who deserves to get hurt in order to create it.

text:
the picture on the left is me 12 years ago! then a victim now a victor! .
.
i am one of the few fortunate to be alive. some  left in a body bag and while many still suffer domestic violence because it remains widespread and is often considered "socially acceptable‚Äù in nigeria. .
.
this is the reason family, friends and even some religious bodies do not see domestic violence as such a big deal. they believe it‚Äôs the outcome of provocation and admonish victims never to annoy their abusers . but these abusers don‚Äôt hit their bosses or colleagues who provoke them at work . they exercise restraints! .

domestic violence is not a result of provocation. i‚Äôm writing this in capital letters and i hope it sinks in! violence and abuse is a tool used to enforce control, power and fear in a relationship or marriage and not a momentary expression of anger.
.
so stop judging victims by saying they were battered because of an imagined, perceived or rumored wrong or asking them annoying questions like ‚Äúwhat did you do that made him beat you‚Äù. questions like these are unintelligent and insensitive.
.
violence against women isn't cultural, its criminal. real men don't use violence! we must all join hands to eliminate violence against women and girls. our women must feel and know that they are not alone! .

there is no excuse for violence against women.  and yes, no excuse for violence against men either. 
don't justify it....don't judge them!
.
i am a victim turned victor ready to help other victims. join in , let's make a difference! .
.

ŸÅÿπÿßŸÑÿßŸÜ ÿ≠ŸÇŸàŸÇ ÿ®ÿ¥ÿ± ŸÜÿ≥ÿ®ÿ™ ÿ™ÿµŸÖ€åŸÖ ÿØŸàŸÑÿ™ ÿ¥€åŸÑ€å ÿ®ÿ±ÿß€å ŸÜÿßŸÖ⁄Øÿ∞ÿßÿ±€å €å⁄©€å ÿßÿ≤ ŸÖŸáŸÖ‚Äåÿ™ÿ±€åŸÜ ŸÅÿ±ŸàÿØ⁄ØÿßŸá‚ÄåŸáÿß€å ÿß€åŸÜ ⁄©ÿ¥Ÿàÿ± ÿ®Ÿá ŸÜÿßŸÖ ¬´Ÿæÿßÿ®ŸÑŸà ŸÜÿ±ŸàÿØÿß¬ª ÿ¥ÿßÿπÿ± ÿ®ÿ±ŸÜÿØŸá ŸÜŸàÿ®ŸÑ ÿßÿØÿ®€åÿßÿ™ ÿßÿπÿ™ÿ±ÿßÿ∂ ⁄©ÿ±ÿØŸÜÿØ.

ÿ®Ÿá ⁄Øÿ≤ÿßÿ±ÿ¥ ÿß€åÿ≥ŸÜÿß ÿ®Ÿá ŸÜŸÇŸÑ ÿßÿ≤ ⁄Øÿßÿ±ÿØ€åŸÜÿå ¬´Ÿæÿßÿ®ŸÑŸà ŸÜÿ±ŸàÿØÿß¬ª ŸÜŸà€åÿ≥ŸÜÿØŸá ÿ®ÿ±ŸÜÿØŸá ŸÜŸàÿ®ŸÑ ÿßÿ®€åÿßÿ™ ÿ®ŸàÿØ ⁄©Ÿá ÿ®ÿß ÿ¥ÿπÿ±Ÿáÿß€åÿ¥ ÿ®Ÿá ÿ≤ŸÜÿØ⁄Ø€å Ÿà ÿØÿ¥Ÿàÿßÿ±€å‚ÄåŸáÿß€å ÿ≤ŸÜÿØ⁄Ø€å ŸÖÿ±ÿØŸÖ ŸÖÿπŸÖŸàŸÑ€å ÿ¢ŸÖÿ±€å⁄©ÿß€å ŸÑÿßÿ™€åŸÜ ŸÖ€å‚ÄåŸæÿ±ÿØÿßÿÆÿ™ Ÿà ÿ≤ŸÜÿØ⁄Ø€å ÿßŸà ÿ®Ÿá ÿπŸÜŸàÿßŸÜ ŸÜŸÖÿßÿØ€å ÿßÿ≤ ŸÖŸÇÿßŸàŸÖÿ™ ÿØÿ± ŸÖŸÇÿßÿ®ŸÑ ÿØ€å⁄©ÿ™ÿßÿ™Ÿàÿ±€å ÿ¥ŸÜÿßÿÆÿ™Ÿá ŸÖ€å‚Äåÿ¥ŸàÿØ. 
ÿ®ÿß ÿß€åŸÜ Ÿàÿ¨ŸàÿØ ÿ™ÿµ€åŸÖ€åŸÖ ÿßÿÆ€åÿ± ÿ¥€åŸÑ€å ÿ®ÿ±ÿß€å ŸÜÿßŸÖ ŸÜŸáÿßÿØŸÜ €å⁄©€å ÿßÿ≤ ÿ¥ŸÑŸàÿ∫‚Äåÿ™ÿ±€åŸÜ ŸÅÿ±ŸàÿØ⁄ØÿßŸá‚ÄåŸáÿß€å ÿß€åŸÜ ⁄©ÿ¥Ÿàÿ± ÿ®Ÿá ŸÜÿßŸÖ ÿß€åŸÜ ⁄ÜŸáÿ±Ÿá ÿßÿØÿ®€å ÿ®ÿß ÿßÿπÿ™ÿ±ÿßÿ∂ÿßÿ™ ŸÅÿ±ÿßŸàÿßŸÜ ŸÅÿπÿßŸÑÿßŸÜ ÿ≠ŸÇŸàŸÇ ÿ®ÿ¥ÿ± ÿ±Ÿà ÿ®Ÿá ÿ±Ÿà ÿ¥ÿØŸá ÿßÿ≥ÿ™ ⁄Üÿ±ÿß ⁄©Ÿá ÿ¢ŸÜ‚ÄåŸáÿß ŸÖÿπÿ™ŸÇÿØŸÜÿØ ÿß€åŸÜ ÿßŸÅÿ™ÿÆÿßÿ± ÿ¥ÿß€åÿ≥ÿ™Ÿá ⁄©ÿ≥€å ŸÜ€åÿ≥ÿ™ ⁄©Ÿá ÿØÿ± €å⁄©€å ÿßÿ≤ ÿ¢ÿ´ÿßÿ±ÿ¥ ÿ®Ÿá ÿ™ÿ¨ÿßŸàÿ≤ ÿßÿπÿ™ÿ±ÿßŸÅ ⁄©ÿ±ÿØŸá ÿßÿ≥ÿ™. 
⁄©ŸÖ€åÿ™Ÿá ŸÅÿ±ŸáŸÜ⁄Ø€å ŸÖÿ¨ŸÑÿ≥ ÿ≥ŸèŸÅŸÑÿß€å ÿ¥€åŸÑ€å ÿß€åŸÜ ŸÖÿßŸá Ÿà ÿ®ÿß ÿ±ÿß€å‚Äå⁄Ø€åÿ±€å ÿßÿπŸÑÿßŸÖ ⁄©ÿ±ÿØ ⁄©Ÿá ŸÇÿ±ÿßÿ± ÿßÿ≥ÿ™ ŸÅÿ±ŸàÿØ⁄ØÿßŸá ¬´ÿ≥ÿßŸÜÿ™€åÿß⁄ØŸà¬ª ÿß€åŸÜ ⁄©ÿ¥Ÿàÿ± ÿ±ÿß ÿ®Ÿá ŸÜÿßŸÖ ¬´Ÿæÿßÿ®ŸÑŸà ŸÜÿ±ŸàÿØÿß¬ª ÿ™ÿ∫€å€åÿ± ŸÜÿßŸÖ ÿØŸáÿØ. ¬´⁄©ÿßÿ±ŸàŸÑ€åŸÜÿß ŸÖÿßÿ±ÿ≤ŸÜ¬ª €å⁄©€å ÿßÿ≤ ŸÜŸÖÿß€åŸÜÿØ⁄ØÿßŸÜ ŸÖÿ¨ŸÑÿ≥ ÿ¥€åŸÑ€å Ÿà ŸÖŸàÿßŸÅŸÇ ÿß€åŸÜ ÿ∑ÿ±ÿ≠ ⁄ØŸÅÿ™ ŸÜÿßŸÖ ¬´ŸÜÿ±ŸàÿØÿß¬ª ÿ®Ÿá ÿπŸÜŸàÿßŸÜ ⁄©ÿ≥€å ⁄©Ÿá ŸÖŸàÿ¨ÿ® ÿßŸÅÿ™ÿÆÿßÿ± Ÿà ÿ∫ÿ±Ÿàÿ± ŸáŸÖŸá ÿ¥€åŸÑ€åÿß€å€å‚ÄåŸáÿßÿ≥ÿ™ ÿ®ÿß€åÿØ ÿßŸàŸÑ€åŸÜ ⁄Ü€åÿ≤€å ÿ®ÿßÿ¥ÿØ ⁄©Ÿá ÿ®ÿßÿ≤ÿØ€åÿØ⁄©ŸÜŸÜÿØ⁄ØÿßŸÜ ÿ®ÿß Ÿàÿ±ŸàÿØ ÿ®Ÿá ⁄©ÿ¥Ÿàÿ± ÿ¢ŸÜ ÿ±ÿß ŸÖ€å‚Äåÿ®€åŸÜŸÜÿØ. 
ÿØÿ± ⁄ÜŸÜÿØ ŸàŸÇÿ™ ÿßÿÆ€åÿ± ÿßŸÜÿ¨ÿßŸÖ ⁄ÜŸÜÿØ€åŸÜ ÿßÿπÿ™ÿ±ÿßÿ∂ ÿØÿßŸÜÿ¥ÿ¨Ÿà€å€å ÿπŸÑ€åŸá ¬´Ÿæÿßÿ®ŸÑŸà ŸÜŸàÿ±ÿØÿß¬ª  ÿØÿ± ÿ¥€åŸÑ€å ⁄©Ÿá ÿ∫ÿßŸÑÿ®ÿß ÿ™Ÿàÿ≥ÿ∑ ÿ™ÿ¥⁄©ŸÑ‚ÄåŸáÿß€å ŸÅŸÖ€åŸÜ€åÿ≥ÿ™€å ÿßŸÜÿ¨ÿßŸÖ ÿ¥ÿØŸáÿå ÿ¥Ÿáÿ±ÿ™ ÿß€åŸÜ ŸÜŸà€åÿ≥ŸÜÿØŸá Ÿà ÿ¥ÿßÿπÿ± ŸÜÿßŸÖÿØÿßÿ± ÿ±ÿß ÿ®Ÿá ŸÖÿÆÿßÿ∑ÿ±Ÿá ÿßŸÜÿØÿßÿÆÿ™Ÿá ÿßÿ≥ÿ™. ¬´⁄©ÿßÿ±ŸÜ Ÿàÿ±⁄Øÿßÿ±ÿß ÿ≥ÿßŸÜ⁄Üÿ≤¬ª ŸÅÿπÿßŸÑ ÿØÿßŸÜÿ¥ÿ¨Ÿà€å€å ŸÖÿπÿ™ŸÇÿØ ÿßÿ≥ÿ™ ÿØŸÑ€åŸÑ Ÿàÿßÿ∂ÿ≠ Ÿà ÿ±Ÿàÿ¥ŸÜ€å ÿ®ÿ±ÿß€å ÿ™ÿ∫€å€åÿ± ŸÜÿßŸÖ ŸÅÿ±ŸàÿØ⁄ØÿßŸá Ÿàÿ¨ŸàÿØ ŸÜÿØÿßÿ±ÿØÿå ÿ¢ŸÜ ŸáŸÖ ÿØÿ± ÿ≤ŸÖÿßŸÜ€å ⁄©Ÿá ÿ≤ŸÜÿßŸÜ ÿ®ÿß ÿ¥ÿ±Ÿàÿπ ÿ¨ŸÜÿ®ÿ¥‚ÄåŸáÿß€å€å ⁄ÜŸàŸÜ #metoo ÿØÿ± ÿ™ŸÑÿßÿ¥ Ÿáÿ≥ÿ™ŸÜÿØ ÿ™ÿß ÿ≥Ÿàÿ° ÿßÿ≥ÿ™ŸÅÿßÿØŸá‚Äå⁄©ŸÜŸÜÿØ⁄ØÿßŸÜ ÿ¨ŸÜÿ≥€å ÿ±ÿß ŸÖÿ≠⁄©ŸàŸÖ ⁄©ŸÜŸÜÿØ. 
ÿß€åŸÜ ÿ¨ŸÜÿ¨ÿßŸÑ‚ÄåŸáÿß ŸáŸÖ⁄Ø€å ÿ®Ÿá ÿØŸÑ€åŸÑ ÿµŸÅÿ≠Ÿá‚Äåÿß€å ÿßÿ≤ ⁄©ÿ™ÿßÿ® ÿÆÿßÿ∑ÿ±ÿßÿ™ ¬´ŸÜÿ±ŸàÿØÿß¬ª ÿßÿ≥ÿ™ ⁄©Ÿá ÿØÿ± ÿ¢ŸÜ ÿ®Ÿá ÿ™ÿ¨ÿßŸàÿ≤ ÿ®Ÿá ÿ≤ŸÜ ÿÆÿØŸÖÿ™⁄©ÿßÿ± ÿØÿ± ÿ≥ÿßŸÑ €±€π€≤€π ÿßÿπÿ™ÿ±ÿßŸÅ ŸÖ€å‚Äå⁄©ŸÜÿØ. ÿß⁄Øÿ±⁄ÜŸá ÿß€åŸÜ ⁄©ÿ™ÿßÿ® ÿÆÿßÿ∑ÿ±ÿßÿ™ ÿ®€åÿ¥ ÿßÿ≤ €¥€∞ ÿ≥ÿßŸÑ Ÿæ€åÿ¥ ŸÖŸÜÿ™ÿ¥ÿ± ÿ¥ÿØŸá ÿßÿ≥ÿ™ ÿßŸÖÿß ÿß€åŸÜ ÿ®ÿÆÿ¥ ÿßÿ≤ ÿÆÿßÿ∑ÿ±ÿßÿ™ ÿØÿ± ÿ≥ÿßŸÑ‚ÄåŸáÿß€å ÿßÿÆ€åÿ± ŸÖŸàÿ±ÿØ ÿ™Ÿàÿ¨Ÿá Ÿà ŸÖÿ≠ŸÑ ÿ®ÿ≠ÿ´ Ÿà ÿ¨ŸÜÿ¨ÿßŸÑ ÿ¥ÿØŸá ÿßÿ≥ÿ™. ¬´ÿß€åÿ≤ÿßÿ®ŸÑ ÿ¢ŸÑŸÜÿØŸá¬ª ŸÜŸà€åÿ≥ŸÜÿØŸá ŸÖÿ∑ÿ±ÿ≠ ÿ¥€åŸÑ€åÿß€å€å Ÿà ŸÅÿπÿßŸÑ ÿ≠ŸÇŸàŸÇ ÿ≤ŸÜÿßŸÜ ŸÜ€åÿ≤ ŸÖÿπÿ™ŸÇÿØ ÿßÿ≥ÿ™ ⁄©Ÿá ÿ¢ÿ´ÿßÿ± ¬´ŸÜÿ±ŸàÿØÿß¬ª ŸáŸÜŸàÿ≤ ÿßÿ±ÿ≤ÿ¥ŸÖŸÜÿØ Ÿáÿ≥ÿ™ŸÜÿØ ÿßŸÖÿß ŸÖŸÜ ŸÜ€åÿ≤ ŸÖÿ¥ÿßÿ®Ÿá ÿ®ÿ≥€åÿßÿ±€å ÿ∑ÿ±ŸÅÿØÿßÿ±ÿßŸÜ ÿ¨ŸàÿßŸÜ ÿ≠ŸÇŸàŸÇ ÿ≤ŸÜÿßŸÜ ÿØÿ± ÿ¥€åŸÑ€å ÿßÿ≤ ÿ®ÿ±ÿÆ€å ÿßÿ≤ ÿßÿ®ÿπÿßÿØ ÿ≤ŸÜÿØ⁄Ø€å Ÿà ÿ¥ÿÆÿµ€åÿ™ ¬´Ÿæÿßÿ®ŸÑŸà ŸÜÿ±ŸàÿØÿß¬ª ŸÖŸÜÿ≤ÿ¨ÿ± Ÿáÿ≥ÿ™ŸÖ ÿßŸÖÿß ÿ®ÿß ÿß€åŸÜ Ÿàÿ¨ŸàÿØ ŸÜŸÖ€å‚Äåÿ™ŸàÿßŸÜ ŸÜŸàÿ¥ÿ™Ÿá‚ÄåŸáÿß€å ÿßŸà ÿ±ÿß ŸÜÿßÿØ€åÿØŸá ⁄Øÿ±ŸÅÿ™. ÿ™ÿπÿØÿßÿØ ⁄©ŸÖ€å ÿßÿ≤ ÿßŸÅÿ±ÿßÿØ ÿ®Ÿà€å⁄òŸá ŸÖÿ±ÿØÿßŸÜ ÿµÿßÿ≠ÿ® ŸÇÿØÿ±ÿ™ Ÿà ŸÜŸÅŸàÿ∞ ÿ±ŸÅÿ™ÿßÿ±Ÿáÿß€å ŸÇÿßÿ®ŸÑ ÿ™ÿ≠ÿ≥€åŸÜ€å ÿØÿßÿ±ŸÜÿØ Ÿà ŸÖÿ™ÿßÿ≥ŸÅÿßŸÜŸá ¬´ŸÜÿ±ŸàÿØÿß¬ª ŸÅÿ±ÿØ€å ÿÆÿ∑ÿß⁄©ÿßÿ± ÿ®ŸàÿØÿå ŸáŸÖ⁄ÜŸàŸÜ ŸáŸÖŸá ŸÖÿß ⁄©Ÿá ÿ®Ÿá ŸÜÿ≠Ÿà€å ÿÆÿ∑ÿß ŸÖ€å‚Äå⁄©€åŸÜŸÖ.

text:
25 november is international day for the elimination of violence against women.

1 in 3 women experiences physical or sexual violence in their lifetime, usually from a male partner. this inflicts deep physical and psychological wounds. worst, girls and women are left without recourse or justice, forced to continue living under threat, often side by side with perpetrators enjoying impunity.

we must break the silence and speak out. we must stop seeing women as victims, to empower them as forces of change in their lives and communities. we must start as early as possible, with girls, on the benches of schools.

our position is clear. violence does not just harm women, it weakens societies as a whole. at a time when all countries are seeking new sources of creativity and dynamism, no one can be left behind, no society can afford to discriminate against half of its population, half of its imagination, half of its ingenuity.

the rights and dignity of girls and women are foundations for a better future for all. this is why we must eliminate all violence against women. @unesco

text:
.‚Å£‚Å£
my name is gaby @gaby_tsu & i created this page with @izzy.mcdowell ‚ù§Ô∏èüôåüèª ‚Å£‚Å£
‚Å£‚Å£
we decided to take part in the 16 days of activism against gender-based violence campaign (from 25 november, the international day for the elimination of violence against women, to 10 december, human rights day) which is a time to galvanize action to end violence against women and girls around the world.‚Å£‚Å£
‚Å£
‚Å£
before asking other girls to speak up about their own experiences, i thought i should share my own story. ‚Å£
‚Å£
‚Å£
i was in  toxic relationships as almost all of the men i have been in relationships were violent in many different ways.‚Å£‚Å£
‚Å£
‚Å£
please remember that violence is not just physical but also psychological harm.‚Å£‚Å£
‚Å£
‚Å£
according to @whiteribbonaust ‚Å£‚Å£
a woman may be experiencing abuse if a man in her life:‚Å£‚Å£
‚Å£
‚Å£
‚Ä¢ unfairly & regularly accuses her of flirting or being unfaithful;
‚Ä¢ controls how she spends money‚Å£‚Å£;
‚Ä¢ decides what she wears or eats‚Å£‚Å£;
‚Ä¢ umiliate her in front of other people‚Å£‚Å£;
‚Ä¢ monitors what she is doing, including reading her emails & text messages‚Å£‚Å£;
‚Ä¢ discourages or prevents her from seeing friends & family‚Å£‚Å£;
‚Ä¢ threatens to hurt her, the children or pets;
‚Ä¢ physically assaults her (hitting, biting, slapping, kicking, pushing);
‚Ä¢ yells at her;
‚Ä¢ constantly compares her with other people; and/or
‚Ä¢ constantly criticises her intelligence, mental health & appearance.
‚Å£‚Å£
‚Å£‚Å£
‚Å£‚Å£
‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî- i will be sharing more of my experiences for the next #16days for #hearmetoo #orangetheworld .‚Å£‚Å£
‚Å£‚Å£
if you have experienced any abusive relationships or any assaults let‚Äôs speak up & tag us / use #empowerourwomentoday üåàüôèüèª‚Å£‚Å£
‚Å£‚Å£
‚Å£‚Å£
no more silence.‚Å£‚Å£
‚Å£‚Å£
‚Å£‚Å£
together we are strong and end violence against women!!!!‚Å£‚Å£

text:
those of you who know me know that 6 & 1/2 years ago, i survived not only being raped by two strangers, but also  carrying my first born son from that rape, to full term and through the adoption process. it was the darkest and most difficult time in my life. there were few systems set up to offer how much i needed to heal. from this experience, i learned to actively heal myself, connect with my community, and to help support other women with similar stories-go on. 
my vision is to bring clothed, trauma informed, japanese 5 element shiatsu, thai massage, cupping, guasha, reiki and sound healing directly to the doors of women who need it the most.

since 1 in 3 women suffers from sexual assault,  trauma informed bodywork should be as readily available to women as a lyft ride! of those 1 in 3 women who have survived sexual assault, the majority of them are women of color.

through the recent and widespread #metoo movement, more and more people are coming forward to tell their stories, and we have to support them as they open these wounds and allow themselves to be seen, and work towards healing.

if you believe in my vision to offer trauma informed massage to women who need it most please donate and share today! 
i will be eternally grateful!
how you can help: click on the link below and;
1. donate today- every bit helps and it would mean i could answer this calling in my life for women who need it most!‚ú®
2.donate today and share my campaign! sharing with your friends that you have helped inspires them to jump on board too!üåü
3. like and share my campaign with your friends! even if you can‚Äôt donate $10 maybe you have 10 friends who can! please consider helping spread the word in this way.üôèüèΩ thank you so much!

text:
üíú support comes in many forms, and sometimes it can be hard to know how or what you can do to help someone or something, especially when we are all 'so busy'.
.
everyone has something they can offer or give away; be it money, gifts, time, labour, love. but i believe the best thing you can do for someone is just show up.. show up completely. if that's the one gift you can give someone, the gift of your space and time, then you have already given that person more than you could ever squeeze into a christmas stocking or wrap up in a box. christmas is about giving and sharing, not about spending money, going to the best parties, or getting the hottest handbag or outfit.
.
here at wrl we are actively giving away the gift of our time, not only this christmas, but from every day forward since i started on this journey. yes i love to donate gifts for causes and events where i can, but my my most treasured asset will always be the gift & exchange of being present üôá‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è
.
i'd like to thank these ladies for all of their support lately. they have proven to me what i have been feeling: you can't measure love by what people give you or don't give you. love is always present, because love is in the heart, the eyes, the soul, the hands... love is in us all. it's all about connection, showing up, being honest enough to be vulnerable enough to show people the real you. wow. thank you ladies for the beautiful gift of support, friendship, sisterhood, acceptance, humility, integrity and positivity. i am rich! ‚òÄÔ∏è
.

text:
8 things i do, despite being told not to:
.
1. discuss religion & politics at supper.
2. watch narcos mexico (weak, netflix).
3. wear my production clothes and help set up before every event. 
4. swerve the car to save an animal.
5. refuse to politely fake-laugh at #metoo jokes & how "difficult it is for men to even banter now". awle poor lads.
6. immediately delete emails that state "revert back asap".
7. look at everyone with an (un)healthy dose of skepticism. minus dogs & ellies.
8. never eat/dress/stand/sit/look/speak/laugh "like a girl".
.
.
.
.
thank you @influentialwomenoftheworld for the mention. fun & funny to be awarded for being anything but.

text:
this photo might just be a candid mirror selfie, but there is so much behind this photo that means the world to me. yesterday was the day where during hot yoga i finally took my top off and wore my sports bra, without worrying about the consequences. i even left the room without it on and being able to walk down the stairs at the gym owning my body for the first time in months where i haven‚Äôt felt his control felt amazing. this is the first time i‚Äôve gotten changed in the gym changing rooms without worrying about if women can see his scratch marks he left on my boobs after that time i didn‚Äôt wear a bra and he tried to pull my nipples off. i didn‚Äôt realise how much control he had of me. the clothes i wear to work are chosen by me and only me, what i wear to the beach and to the gym is my choiceüòÅ

i may be a person that seems very confident in her skin, at times i‚Äôm full of confidence. but the gym is a completely different space for me, it was his place. he knew people looked at what was his and he didn‚Äôt like that. being able to get changed in a gym bathroom that‚Äôs open plan is huge for me. taking a shirt off in hot yoga is huge for me. being able to be comfortable in my own skin without thinking that he‚Äôs going to criticise me is huge for me. life is so precious üåøand it‚Äôs so important to learn, that no man can ever tell you what you can or can‚Äôt do, wear or act. if he‚Äôs telling you that you can‚Äôt ever go braless, show off too much of your legs, wear things that show too much skin. run for the hills. if he‚Äôs telling you what to wear, how to act, who you can or cannot hang out with or talk to, it is a sign of emotional abuse. and that is not okay! üí™üèΩ#metoo #offmychest #hearmetoo #takealoadoff

¬øo estamos apu√±alandonos entre nosotras mismas?

text:
tomorrow is #givingtuesday, and we are going to be selling these t-shirts to raise funds so we can reach more people with ptsd!
for every dollar raised we can reach 22 people suffering with ptsd.
this is going to be used to reach more people on facebook and give them free resources to help them through their recovery, things like free books, access to our free facebook group, videos, and just overall support.
it's about building awareness about the resources and tools that people suffering can get for free.
there are so many people out there who don't have anyone, or anything to support them.
and a lot of people don't even know that they even have ptsd so it's to help get in front of them and give them the support and love, and really a place for them to come so they can get the help and guidance they need!
thank you for everything <3 hope you have a great rest of your day!!

text:
tbt to this summer. i walked with the dead. every pun intended. i went as spectator at  the zombie walk in stockholm.

in another way i felt more dead than alive. working harder than ever. long shifts, no rest, no time for myself. get home after double shifts and have even more work at home. no safe place to retreat to for recreation and well deserved rest. more dead than alive.

now, i try to spend more time and effort on myself. rebuilding my inner strength, find safe haven. create. trying to feel a sensation of freedom, choice rather than must. 
today i feel a bit better than i have in a long while. for more reasons than i can explain. but one of the biggest reasons is that nine days ago i underwent a complicated surgery to remove old torture scars. for over 8 years i had them. looking in the mirror,  all i could see was their faces, hear their laugh, and feel that tingling sharp pain where the box cutter separated my skin. the surgery might have left me with another scar, and another type of pain. but that pain will go away. now atleast i can't see their faces anymore. when i look in the mirror, i dont see their faces, i only see myself. and now-for the first time in years, i'm finally going to focus on all the things that make me happy, and allow myself to heal. 
#metoo #heal #walkingdead #goth #gingergoth #gothgirl #alternative #selflove

text:
i am standing for #orangetheworld campaign by unwomen. @unwomen 
i believe that child marriage is a form of violence against women and girls.

tulisan ini adalah suara saya dan putri*(rekan saya sebagai korban pernikahan dini), gadis, dan wanita yang pernah mengalami dan atau orang tua yang menginginkan anaknya untuk menikah dini.

tidak sedikit orang tua yang berfikir bahwa pernikahan dini adalah salah satu kunci terbaik untuk menyelamatkan anak dari hal - hal buruk di lingkungannya.
siapa yang bisa menjamin anak lolos dari kekerasan seksual dan pergaulan bebas jika ia telah terikat di suatu pernikahan paksa?

sebuah keputusan yang telah orang tua mereka buat, yang tanpa sadar telah merenggut hak mereka untuk menikmati hidup dengan pilihan mereka sendiri.

baru ‚Äì baru ini telah terjadi pembunuhan dengan modus kecemburuan di kota samarinda ( samarinda seberang ) yang dilakukan oleh suami putri (17 tahun) seorang gadis korban pernikahan dini diatas tuntutan ego orang tuanya. 
dari tulisan ini, saya berharap ada lebih banyak orang yang berbaris di barisan juang menyuarakan bahwa pernikahan dini bukan penyelesaian atas masalah ekonomi, budaya, kekerabatan dsb.

di indonesia pernikahan dini didominasi oleh anak dengan usia sebelum umur 18 tahun.

lalu berdasarkan hukum yang berlaku, usia berapa seseorang dikatakan sebagai anak?

berdasarkan beberapa ketentuan dalam peraturan perundang ‚Äì undangan yang ada di indonesia tidak ditemui kesamaan yang pasti hingga usia berapakah seseorang bisa dikatakan sebagai anak. sebagian memberi batasan 21 ( dua puluh satu) tahun, 18 (delapan belas), 17 (tujuh belas). hal ini dirasa mengganjal, pada uu perkawinan yang berlaku di indonesia dinyatakan bahwa usia 19 tahun bagi laki-laki dan 16 tahun bagi perempuan bisa melangsungkan pernikahan disertai dengan syarat pernikahan dibawah 21 tahun harus mempunyai izin orang tua. (keterangan di foto selanjutnya). jika memang pernikahan dini terjadi dibawah umur 18 tahun dan dengan izin orang tua, bisa dikatakan bahwa orang tua telah melakukan violence terhadap anaknya sendiri.

dari tulisan ini, saya berharap ada lebih banyak orang yang berbaris di barisan juang menyuarakan bahwa pernikahan dini bukan penyelesaian atas masalah ekonomi, budaya, kekerabatan dsb.

di indonesia pernikahan dini didominasi oleh anak dengan usia sebelum umur 18 tahun.

lalu berdasarkan hukum yang berlaku, usia berapa seseorang dikatakan sebagai anak?

berdasarkan beberapa ketentuan dalam peraturan perundang ‚Äì undangan yang ada di indonesia tidak ditemui kesamaan yang pasti hingga usia berapakah seseorang bisa dikatakan sebagai anak. sebagian memberi batasan 21 ( dua puluh satu) tahun, 18 (delapan belas), 17 (tujuh belas). hal ini dirasa mengganjal, pada uu perkawi yang berlaku di indonesia dinyatakan bahwa usia 19 tahun bagi laki-laki dan 16 tahun bagi perempuan bisa melangsungkan pernikahan diseai dengan syarat pernikahan dibawah 21 tahun harus mempunyai izin orang tua. (keterangan di foto selanjutnya). jika memang pernikahan dini terjadi dibawah umur 18 tahun dan dengan izin orang tua, bisa dikatakan bahwa orang tua telah melakukan violence terhadap anaknya sendiri.

text:
where there is violence and abuse, there is no love. ---
last year, we wrote a book for survivors of violence in #afghanistan and around the world. to this day, it has been downloaded in persian and pashtu nearly 1500 times, more than 80 english copies have been bought to support our work, and hundreds of copies have been distributed in kabul, balkh, sar-e-pul, herat, and most recently, khost provinces. for 16 days of activism against violence against women, we will be sharing some key quotes from the book.

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text: the past day or so a lot of past trauma snuck up on me. i was listening to a podcast which triggered some not so great memories. memories of my world and my life not being mine. memories that i tried long to forget. memories i wanted no part of. memories that questioned my worth as a human. memories of my body not being mine. it‚Äôs been years since they occurred. years since the trauma. but it struck me yesterday. what happened to be wasn‚Äôt okay or normal. i tend to normalize things. say things that happened to me wasn‚Äôt so bad. that it just happened to me - not to others by the same person. what happened to me is in the past. i can‚Äôt change it. but i need to heal the wounds (hello therapy!). my anxiety and depression have grown in those years.  i have great people in my life now. ones that i know won‚Äôt treat me like that. but that doesn‚Äôt make it easily go away either. i am putting in the work.

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
#metoo  #metoomovement
.
the¬†shocking truth. 1/6 women,  1/33 men, 1/7 children experience sexual assult in thier lifetime. every 2 miniutes someone is sexually assulted. unfortunatly its one of the only crimes that the victim is guilty untill proven innocent. only 22% felt posituve after talking to the police. a whole 71% felt negativly, abandoned and devastated. the only cause of rape and sexual assault is the perpetrator
.
i have been raped twice and sexually assaulted
.
november 2016 - i had been missing for 5 hours, my parents on the phone to the police. i reported what happened. an investigation that lasted 10 months. the case was taken very seriously. dna tests, cctv, forensic examinations, interviews etc. untill they saw my medical records. that day they came to the conclusion because of my past mental health that i was to blame. that i must of done something that caused it. i put myself in a situation that i asked for it. i was humiliated, devastated, broken. it effects ones inner most sense of self and dignity. hearing someone else say the words that so many victims already believe
.
its taken me alot of time to heal, to feel safe. to overcome flashbacks, terror, mistrust etc. it was not my fault. it never was
.
there is no excuse for rape. it doesnt matter how we are dressed, who we were with, what time of day it is, if we were flirting. we have the right to dress how we want, drink, go out where we want. we have the right to live our lives. it can happen to anyone. passed out, spiked, 'stop, leave me alone, get away, dont', turning away, being underaged means no. its not your fault if you didnt know how to stop them or put up a fight, regardless if they are your boyfriend or girlfriend or know them
.
our bodies belong to us as individuals and no one else
.
being forced against your will is a crime
.
although my case was closed, the devastation from it and he walks free i am glad i reported it. his dna remains in the system. perpetrators shouldn't be protected by our silence
.
this is my message to you. don't suffer in silence. it hard to trust, to talk. there is help out there. you are not to blame. there is life after sexual assault and rape.

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

text: i am posting today, to say that after 1.5 years of trauma, counselling, and staying quiet, i went to ottawa police on saturday and am pressing charges. i have watched a woman in my life completely fall apart after an assault from her past corrupted her psychologically. i will not let that happen to me. i am not proud to say that i was sexually assaulted, but i am proud to tell you, i reported. going to the police seems terrifying and daunting, but it‚Äôs the right things to do. if you or someone you know has been assaulted, i urge you to go to the police and report it. we are stronger together. you are not only protecting yourself, but you are protecting women who could be assaulted in the future. #metoo #metoomovement #endrapeculture #orangetheworld #enddomesticviolence #survivor #consent #bbg #strongwomen #reportabuse #hearmetoo #believesurvivors

please join #cfawl and @ocbayls for a free cle luncheon on friday, november 30, 2018, at the orange county courthouse in the judicial conference room. the topic of the luncheon is the legal ramifications of #metoo. a distinguished panel of speakers will be led by moderator mary ann morgan, former ocba president and member of the florida bar board of governors.

check-in begins at 11:45, lunch is from noon to 1:00 pm, and an optional discussion will follow. the event is free to everyone. 1.0 cle credit is expected. please rsvp to lauren.millcarek@hklaw.com by wednesday, november 28. we look forward to seeing you there! #cfawlconnects #ylslearns

text:
you dont have to live in the gym or be a gym rat to be healthy & fit!
-
-
i know a few of you out there think i‚Äôm all about exercise and live in the gym however i am holistic (mental, emotional, physical, spiritual) nothing is more powerful than made up mind.
-
-
in my workshops and lectures i typically talk about the biggest leverage points being: consistent with functional movement (walking #1 exercise), fine-tuning your nutrition and micro nutrition, proper sleep hygiene and being honest by assessing your stress levels.
-
-
for the past year i‚Äôve been dedicated to building strength in my body, it feels amazing to have strength and integration of upper and lower body with the core. the technology and knowledge i got from the @chekinstitute & @paul.chek helped me to put it together systematically for myself first and help others from a place if applied knowledge.
-
-
for many years i‚Äôve heard of clients, friends and followers share their stories about having serious problems with autoimmune issues from limes disease to ms, crohn‚Äôs or lupus. -
-
having gone through it myself and healed at 100%, i can be an example of what is possible. so in the end, my dedication to what i‚Äôm creating is based on my own journey to self love and fortunately it‚Äôs attached to my mission of disrupting our ideas of what is not possible.üôè

"after the hit"
last night, i went away by train.
leaving the city for my little country.
the spiders were breathing under the wooden floor.
i took a shower, trying to wipe off the blue traces that, your, big fingers did.
the exploded veins looked like massive oceans on my nude legs.
i closed my eyes to be in a total black.
remembering this furniture drawer falling in a noisy silence, breaking my glasses,  i had to think that it could have been my head under this heavy piece of wood.
i open my eyes, finding my air is back.
the ones  who went to visit my house, knows that my bathroom is full of mirrors.
in one of those, i see the reflection of a woman that i don't reconise.
miss shapen i took 10 kilos, love is heavy.
jos√©phine sapin

text: so i painted over a painting i had done with someone i dated that assaulted me. as a form of therapy, i thought painting over it would provide closure, or a sense of it, but instead, i just kept painting all these different colors on top of each other with no purpose and no goal. just let me know after layer. those pretty purple colors at the top across, those were some of the first colors i painted over with, and that was easy, it flowed. but everything in the inside is a wreck. none of it correlates, at all. it looks hectic. i'm not sure what to make of what this means. #painting #therapy #art #creative #metoo #sexualassault #stillirise #always #strength #women #findstrengthwithin #staytrue

i don't speak on the flat earth topic much on this page, because it has nothing to do with you getting the ruach and avoiding the lake. however, when i talk to my friends away from the gram, i tell them this is how i view the earth, because this is how the scriptures describe it.

when people say the earth is a globe, they are thinking of a full circled globe, like a basketball.
that isn't the only type of globe there is, you also have the half circle globe, like we see in the snow globe toys.

the snow globe toys have been around for hundred of years, and we call them globes without question, yet when you mention the earth being globe people only think of a circular shape.

according to the bible, the earth is the shape of a snow globe toy, a half circle, flat on the bottom with a firmament dome covering the sides and tops.

we cannot confirm either one definitively with our own hand and eyes, because we are restricted from going to the edges of the earth, as well as restricted from going to the top of the earth. of course many of you will say what about the moon landing. that moon landing is and was bullshit, those liars never traveled to the moon, and they never will.

everything this society gives you are a bunch of lies. truth be told we can't prove flat earth, show glove earth or full globe earth, but we can look at the evidence and claims dealing with all three and do the process of elimination.

if you are a sheep that believes in nasa, space explanation, big bang theory and the rest of that nigga shit, then this will surely zoom over your head. if we had the technology to go to the moon decades ago and our equipment and technology has improved considerably since the 50s and 60s, why can't we go today?

think of how much technology has improved in the last 50 years, what's stopping us today?

what's stopping us today, is people being able to u cover those lies today since we have new technology. the first time many people saw television was during the time of the moon walk, so they could make a fool out of them with the shitty graphics, today they can't fool us.

text:
writing has always been cathartic for me. i remember when i was a little girl, i would write in a journal every night before bed. it helped me process my feelings (even if it was something as trivial as who my crush was or why i was upset with my bff). writing in that journal became a lifesaver for me. it was my one and only private space where i could allow myself to be completely honest with how i felt. .
i remember when i was dating my abuser, he saw my journal and laughed at me. he said something along the lines of ‚Äúonly little girls keep diaries.‚Äù i stopped writing after he said that. i found only two journal entries from the time i was dating him, and both were from a time when i felt a sudden shift in our relationship and didn‚Äôt know how else to process it. i‚Äôm sure those two entries helped keep what little sanity i had left. .
and, of course, after i left my abuser, i started writing out my story on her. writing wasn‚Äôt only healing, but it was validating. i remember i would often doubt my story, but i could go back and see what i had written and remember my truth. writing kept me grounded. it kept me from second-guessing myself even when others did.
.
i am so, so incredibly humbled and honored today to say that weareher.net has over 200 stories on it today. over 200 ways for survivors to heal, to empower themselves, and to begin restoring their bodies and minds. writing is incredibly healing, and if you still don‚Äôt believe me, maybe this except from the apa will change your mind. üíôüíú #weareher
.
.
.
#heal #empower #restore #writing #journaling #journal #speakyourtruth #youareenough #believesurvivors #empoweringwomen #narcissisticabuse #survivor #metoo

text:
alas, #bernardobertolucci, who just passed away. he was celebrated throughout his career as a brilliant director, a ‚Äúa genius auteur,‚Äù a ‚Äúmaster.‚Äù his films were undeniably original, stunningly visualized and psychologically complex. i admire many of them. but he was also undeniably a male filmmaker of his generation ‚Äî exploitative of women actors, in particular maria schneider,
an early #metoo survivor and bravely vocal about her exploitation on the set of her first major film, which she said left her feeling ‚Äúa little raped.‚Äù and for which he said he had no regrets. he passed away at the same time as paris‚Äô huge #noustoutes interesectional feminist rally yesterday. i‚Äôve written about last tango in  paris elsewhere, for example on my blog who cares about actresses, which is dedicated to schneider. this is a drawing of schneider and bertolucci - a ‚Äútowering figure‚Äù - in a series of maria studies i did while researching her life - drawn from a film still of them on set in 1972. #mariaschneider #lasttangoinparis #bertolucci #whocaresaboutactresses #awomanapart #awomanapartfilm

the bigger issue still is that requqlicans are willingly piggybacking this lunacy and abusing the faith of their fellow men while campaigning for the midterms. this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
i am thrilled to announce the official launching of rise (recovery, insight, & survivor empowerment), a 10-week therapeutic support group for women-identified survivors of sexual trauma.
‚Ä¢
‚Ä¢
over the last year, i have poured my heart & soul into the development of this group to ensure that each 90-minute session is deeply impactful & rooted in the most innovative & effective therapeutic interventions for survivors.
‚Ä¢
‚Ä¢
during rise, members will connect with others who have had similar experiences, engage in healing discussions that explore the impact of trauma, & build neuroscience-based coping skills necessary to thrive in today‚Äôs world.¬†upon completion, members will have a customized wellness plan that they may carry into daily life with a newfound sense of strength, control, & resiliency.
‚Ä¢
‚Ä¢
for more information on rise, please visit www.drtruitt.com (link in bio). if you‚Äôre interested in scheduling a complimentary 30-minute phone consultation to assess if this is the right group for you, please call us at 626.524.5525 or email us at info@drtruitt.com!

the other half of the population has been on the receiving end of abuse, neglect and violence in different forms, through various stages of their lives. abuse of women and girls - as a social menace, makes no exception; it is prevalent across different layers of caste, culture and education. crime rates reach a new high every passing day with more and more women feeling unsafe in their immediate environment. 
save the children stands strong with the global voice against gender-based violence! 
we have been on our toes, empowering women across the nation and helping them transform their lives.
for the next 16 days, we will share gripping stories of change, hope and most importantly win against all odds. it‚Äôs time to end violence against women and girls.
 together we shall #orangetheworld

text:
hi all-my name is kaitlin and i am awakening's marketing coordinator! #givingtuesday is coming up and i wanted to share why awakenings is so important to me and how you can help us continue to fight for survivors! my entire life has been impacted by sexual assault, and rather than run away from it, i have made the conscious choice to face it every day. as a result, i have found empowerment in my constant journey of healing and recently, that journey has led me to working at awakenings, a small arts nonprofit dedicated to making visible the work of survivors. my trauma fed off of silence; however, awakenings strives to break that silence for all survivors. this work is difficult and taxing, but this is work that needs to be done; however, the burden should not solely rest on the shoulders of survivors. you can help shoulder that burden by making a small contribution this holiday season. even a simple $10 donation can help us buy supplies for our art therapy workshops. if you have the ability, please donate to awakenings on #givingtuesday by clicking the link in our bio!
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#chicagoart #chicagononprofit #chicagogallery#sexualassault #advocacy#survivorart #artsed#artwatchers #metoo#believesurvivors#metoomvmt

i know the word feminism is thrown around indiscriminately. everyone is a feminist these days and ofcourse men cannot be feminists according to most feminists. what a load of bs. this video is a beautiful explanation of what is feminism. i was always one to keep screaming and shouting about gender equality even in my teens and i continue to do so even now. i refused to go to my parents house during my pregnancy or after the birth of my child (as mandated by tradition) with the hope that my husband would be an integral part of twils early months and he was as he continues to be even today. for us to be an equitable family. for our at that time unborn child (be it girl or boy) to see a family where roles were not defined based on gender. we wanted to bring up our child had it been a boy to grow up and respect women as being there equal and if it was a girl, for her to know that she can be anything she wants and gender does not define her roles. it‚Äôs the generation of our children who are most likely to change the societal norms that exist today and us as partners have the duty to do so. next time you buy your daughter a barbie and your son a gun, remember that you are pegging them by gender. or even when a kitchen set is bought for your daughter and a car for your son. these are very small and innocent ways in which we thrust gender on our children. for the world to be truly equitable, we need a world without gender. #momlife #parenting #parentingquotes #genderneutral #nonconformist #genderequality #feminism #metoo #womenempowerment #girls #heforshe #genderpaygap #womenleaders #mommyblogger #indianmomblogger #motherhood #kids #moms #dads #life #child #love  #repost @swedense with @get_repost

in the recent past, grassroots activists and survivors, as well as global movements such as ‚Äú#metoo‚Äù, ‚Äú#timesup‚Äù, ‚Äú#balancetonporc‚Äù, ‚Äú#niunamenos‚Äù, ‚Äúhollaback!‚Äù and ‚Äú#totalshutdown‚Äù have converted isolation into global sisterhood. they are making offenders accountable, exposing the prevalence of violence from high office to factory floor. today‚Äôs global movements are setting collective demands for accountability and action and calling for the end of impunity, to ensure the human rights of all women and girls.

text:
today marks the continuation of #16daysofactivism for 2018.

from 25th november, the international day for the elimination of violence against women and girls, to 10th december, human rights day, the¬†16 days of activism against gender-based violence campaign¬†is a time to galvanize action to end violence against women and girls around the world.

the international campaign originated from the first women's global leadership institute coordinated by the center for women's global leadership in 1991.

in recent years, the voices of survivors and activists, through campaigns such as #metoo, #timesup, #niunamenos, #notonemore, #balancetonporc and more locally #lifeinleggings, among others, have reached a crescendo that cannot be silenced any more.

advocates understand that while the names and contexts may differ across geographic locations, women and girls everywhere are experiencing extensive abuse and their stories need to be brought to light.

this year be will represent some stories we have been aware of over the years through the unite campaign‚Äôs global advocacy theme:¬†orange the world: #hearmetoo as a means to bring awareness to what girls face daily.

#endviolence #genderviolence #girls #herstory #heartwork #story #likeagirl #advocacy #awakening #awareness #sdg5 #campaign #barbados #pain #cause #charity #change

text:
"those who have never been in an #abusiverelationship struggle to understand how people remain in one for so long. if somebody was mistreating you, "why did you stick around?" they ask.
.
this is because we are conditioned to believe #abuse is always physical. on tv and in films, we see characters who are obviously evil. they are violent to their partners, shout at them aggressively, or even murder them in a fit of rage. while this does happen, it's not a true representation of the abuse many others experience.
.
unfortunately, for many people, when they try to leave these relationships they are so bonded to their abuser that they return. others don't try to leave at all, and are only freed from the clutches of the abuse when they are discarded.
.
an abusive relationship with a #narcissist or #psychopath tends to follow the same pattern: idealisation, devaluation, and discarding. at some point, the victim will be so broken, the abuser will no longer get any benefit from using them. they may have totally bankrupted them, or destroyed their confidence, or worse, and they move on to their next target.
.
however, once they are gone, the victim - or survivor as thomas calls them at this point - can finally start coming round to the idea they were abused. they can grieve, and finally see the damage that was being done, and realise it wasn't their fault.
.
that's when the healing can really begin, thomas says, and the survivor can realise that they were targeted not because they were weak, but because they had so much to give."
.

 while we have made some advancements towards eradicating violence against women - spain for instance is training more than 600 judges on gender violence and preparing to reform the country‚Äôs laws on sex crimes - we still have a long way to go. just yesterday for example, the people who were protesting in istanbul were greeted by tear gas and were prevented from marching by the police.

text:
sometimes i wonder if he did it on purpose. if he wanted to make me become like him. soulless. alone. 
they say hurt people hurt people. that‚Äôs why i never had a call. or a message. he didn‚Äôt hit me. he just left me in the streets alone after being abused because i had to ‚Äúsurvive by my own‚Äù. he didn‚Äôt curse me. he just talked to me whenever he needed something, then going back to the silent treatment for months. he wasn‚Äôt really mean to me, he was just ‚Äúsincere‚Äù. i couldn‚Äôt really claim nothing. we didn‚Äôt have any partnership. we were nothing. because me trying to connect with you is also trying to cut your wings, right? you could have done it but i wasn‚Äôt the right person, am i wrong? you could have thought better before entering my life and digging a hole for my integrity. i lost three years of my life. i guess you were feeling ok about that. playing with all their bodies and knowing that i would be there waiting for you. you thought that everything was ok, you did nothing. i don‚Äôt deserve a phone call, nothing. i stopped waiting a long time ago. you‚Äôve just wasted my time with all of that manipulation and narcissistic behavior. you made me better. but i will not become like you. never.

text:
i founded rising up adventures because i want to use paddle boarding to help women survivors of trauma.
.
.
.
as a survivor myself, i never stop feeling grateful for ocean air, waves and movement of the board over the water. bringing others out into this incredible world is my life‚Äôs mission.
.
.
.
this is my daughter, visiting me for thanksgiving. she grew up paddle boarding every weekend with me, in hawaii, with dolphins, exploring waterfalls...
.
.
.
i‚Äôm so grateful to have another paddle weekend with my beautiful daughter for thanksgiving.
.
. 
when you paddle with us, your proceeds benefit the development of local adventure therapy groups for survivors of trauma.
.
.

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‚Äòugh. totally ugly‚Äô to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it‚Äôs worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don‚Äôt necessarily know it‚Äôs being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it‚Äôs worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you‚Äôre doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people‚Äôs personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn‚Äôt have seen, and couldn‚Äôt have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, ‚Äúwould work for anyone‚Äù. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they‚Äôre mercenaries. they‚Äôll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it‚Äôs an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing ‚Äì at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public ‚Äì our intimate family connections, our ‚Äúlikes‚Äù, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that‚Äôs expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text: on your journey to healing, there are several questions you might need to consider in order to recognize and appreciate your milestones. "what do i need?" is a great start. your needs may be emotional, mental, spiritual, or physical, and there aren't necessarily any wrong answers. some of your needs may be a little harder to achieve than others, but the idea is to identify and work towards them to be the best version of yourself possible. working with a professional counselor who can help you sort through your list is also a good idea. remember, you are a survivor! #childsexabuseawareness #stopchildsexabuse #childsexabusesurvivor #parentsofchilldsexabusesurvivor #sexualassault #endchildsexabuse #endrapeculture #childabuse #sextrafficking #atlanta #atl #georgia #women #girls #teens #awareness #sexcrimes #rapevictims #rape #victims #children #prevention #trafficking  #survivor #tips #blogger #speaker #metoo #advocate

crimes against women have increased by a staggering 800(+)% in india in the last five decades... no nation for women takes a close, hard look at what makes india unsafe for its women ‚Äì from custodial rapes and honour killings to rapes of minors and trafficking ‚Äì the author uncovers many unpalatable truths behind what we are familiar with as newspaper headlines only

journalist and author priyanka dubey travels through large swathes of india, over a period of six years, to uncover the accounts of disenfranchised women who are caught in the grip of patriarchy and violence.

their voices run through me.

text:
"way forward for the #metoo movement"

we thank our stars to be able to bring together such great minds who will lead the conversation! our invitees will share their thoughts and opinions leading to a discussion where every attendee can share their 2 cents!

speakers - 
surabhi rao ( @_surabhirao ) - renowned fashion model who won the femina miss india 2011 (devine thoughts). she's a communication wiz and hosts personality development sessions in and around navi mumbai 
parvinder kaur - is a professor at khalsa college. also heads their emba cell and is a mentor to alot of student start-ups

mahima kukreja ( @agirlofherwords ) -¬† writer. poet. comic. activist. interested in intersectional feminism and its socio-political and cultural impact on youth. she's also among the initial people responsible for spearheading the #metoo movement on the indian internet

harish iyer ( @iyerharish ) - is a renowned activist for a number of causes, including promoting rights of the lgbtqia community

our host/moderator for the evening is tarun agarwal ( @india.tarun ), founder of icon business forum 
date/time - saturday, 1st dec 2018¬†
time - 5pm to 7pm¬†
address - too much drama, vashi sector 19c, palm beach road, near satra plaza. 
with another ambitious attempt to provoke a conversation, we at @toomd_in believe in the essence of this sacred movement. something that will never let it die are constant conversations on the same.

we need to get together and talk, we need to know other perspectives. we invite everyone to our first discussion in a cosy setup where anyone who attends has a voice. 
a conversation provokes change, and change is constant!

#change #metoo #navimumbai

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green

kita harus ada untuk menemani dan mendengarkan para survivor ketika mereka mulai mengumpulkan keberanian untuk bercerita. kita juga harus ikut berjuang untuk orang-orang yang tidak bisa berjuang untuk dirinya sendiri. something has to be done to make a change and the power of change is in our hand.

hari ini adalah hari kedua 16 days of activism against gender-based violence campaign.
ini adalah waktu kita untuk beraksi mengakhiri kekerasan terhadap perempuan, baik anak, remaja, maupun dewasa di seluruh dunia dan un women dengan 25 influencer indonesian membuat video pendek sebagai bagian dari kampanye to end violence against women.

kampanye tahun ini bertemakan orange the world: #hearmetoo karena suara para survivor dan aktivis melalui kampanye #metoo, #timesup, dan sebagainya telah mencapai puncaknya pada beberapa tahun terakhir ini. meskipun nama dan konteksnya mungkin berbeda di seluruh lokasi, tapi kekerasan tetaplah kekerasan, pelecehan tetaplah pelecehan and their story need to be brought to light.

let yourself be heardüíï‚ú® #hearmetoo

text:
dr fiona vera-grey (bottom left) is an academic at durham university and an expert in sexual violence against women prevention. she has worked in services including rape crisis, and research for 10 - 15 years, it‚Äôs safe to say - she is an incredible woman and she knows her shit! we were blessed to such a knowledgable woman write the foreword to our book. üìñ
she was one of the panelists at our event ‚Äòthe art of consent‚Äô, this is just some of what she had to say - "we need to provide spaces for women and young women to be together and to talk about the way that we‚Äôve been affected by gender socialisation, we‚Äôre taught to take up less space, to reduce ourselves, to doubt ourselves - that really came out of the documentary film, the way were taught to doubt our own experience of something. we know what it is, but we‚Äôre taught to doubt what it is.

art - poetry, film, songs - can connect emotionally, develop empathy, around sexual violence in particular, what we need is for people to connect emotionally because it‚Äôs a hard subject. we want to be defended, we want to be removed from it, we want to find excuses. but it‚Äôs important for us to connect and feel together.‚Äù
üëè
üì∏ by @gorrangorra ‚ú® more photos from the event on the website! (link in bio) and a lil video is coming soon!

text:
on this international day to ending violence against women and girls, intersectional feminist foreign policy are launching their 1st edition of their uninvited women journal, providing a platform for the voices of women who are never seen or heard and certainly not invited to sit around the table on issues that impact their lives. 
when me and shaista aziz set this up last year, we were overwhelmed by the interest and the massive need to have different voices, with real experience, and real issues represented and a different form of leadership. 
a massive thank you to our volunteers nuran y ra and chloe roesch who‚Äôve worked hard putting it all together. and our contributors and the many more women who expressed interest. #endviolenceagainstwomen #hearmetoo #metoo #aidtoo #feminism

text:
every  year from 25 november (the international day for the elimination of violence against women) to 10 december (human rights day) the 16 days of activism against gender-based violence campaign is a time to inspire action to end violence against women and girls around the world.  the campaign was launched in 2008 by un secretary-general ban ki-moon. recently, through campaigns such as #metoo and #timesup, voices of survivors and activists have shown that women and girls everywhere are experiencing extensive abuse and their stories need to be brought to light. therefore the global advocacy theme of this years campain is: orange the world: #hearmetoo

text: victim blaming attitudes really trigger me. when i was in a violent relationship, a friend said that it‚Äôs my fault for putting myself through such hardship. i had a choice, why didn‚Äôt i leave? oh god it still triggers me. and it‚Äôs so common to have this response, from society in general but often from friends, family and people we trust.  let me put one thing straight - all abuse happens because the perpetrator decides to abuse. that‚Äôs it. every speculation about what could have been done to prevent it is irrelevant, useless and traumatises the victim further. victim blaming can come from a person looking for security ‚Äúif it‚Äôs the person‚Äôs fault then it can‚Äôt happen to me, i can prevent it‚Äù. or it can come from arrogance and a false sense of superiority ‚Äúi‚Äôm special this sort of thing only happens to the weak minded‚Äù. but abuse can happen for a wide range of reasons and the only common denominator is the person who decides to abuse. all the people out there who further traumatise abuse victims with your sickening victim blaming and inappropriate blame and questioning - just stop. you‚Äôre being awful human beings. educate yourself, make sure you talk to another human being from the perspective of empathy and kindness. stop being the reason why survivors are afraid to speak up. your attitude sustains the culture in which survivors have to stay in the shadow and bear the burden of their trauma. they really should not have to. fellow survivors - don‚Äôt ever listen to the ignorant voices of victim blaming. it‚Äôs not your fault. it‚Äôs not your fault. it‚Äôs never, ever, ever your fault. #bpd #borderline #mentalhealth #victimblaming #metoo #borderlinepersonalitydisorder #mentalhealthawareness #recovery #domesticviolence #emotionalabuse #abuse #abusesurvivor #recovery #recoveryispossible #recoverywin #abusedwomen #abuseawareness #narcissisticabuse #stopchildabuse #abusesurvivors
