"ŸÖÿ¥ ŸÅÿßŸÉÿ±ÿ© ÿ•ŸÜŸâ ŸÇŸàŸÑÿ™ŸÑŸá ÿ¢Ÿáÿå ŸàŸÑÿß ÿ•ŸÜŸä ŸÇŸÑÿ™ŸÑŸá ŸÑÿ£ÿå ŸÖÿ¥ ŸÅÿßŸÉÿ±ÿ© ÿ•ŸÜŸá ÿ≥ÿ£ŸÑ ÿ£ÿµŸÑÿß"
"ÿ™ŸÑÿßŸÇŸäŸÉŸä ÿ®ŸÄŸäŸÄŸÜŸÄÿ™Ÿä ŸÑŸá ÿ•ŸÜŸÉ ÿπÿßŸäÿ≤ÿ©ÿå ŸÖÿß ŸáŸà ŸáŸÄ Ÿäÿ≥ÿ£ŸÑ ŸÑŸäŸá ÿ•ŸÑÿß ŸÑŸà ŸÉÿßŸÜ ÿ¥ÿßŸÅ Ÿàÿßÿ≠ÿØÿ© ÿ¥ŸÉŸÑŸáÿß ÿπÿßŸäÿ≤ÿ©"

ŸÉÿ™Ÿäÿ± ÿ®ŸÄ Ÿäÿ≠ÿµŸÑŸÜÿß ŸÖŸàÿßŸÇŸÅ ŸÖŸÜ ÿ∫Ÿäÿ± ŸÖŸàÿßŸÅŸÇÿ™ŸÜÿß ŸÅŸä ÿπŸÑÿßŸÇÿ™ŸÜÿß ÿ®ÿßŸÑÿ¢ÿÆÿ±ŸäŸÜÿå ŸÖŸÜ ÿ£ŸàŸÑ ÿ∑ÿ±ŸäŸÇÿ© ÿ≥ŸÑÿßŸÖ ŸÖÿ¥ ÿ≠ÿßÿ®ŸäŸÜŸáÿß ÿ≠ÿ™Ÿâ ŸÑŸà ŸÖŸÜ ÿ≠ÿØ ŸÇÿ±Ÿäÿ®ÿå ŸÑÿ≠ÿØ ÿßŸÑŸÖŸàÿßŸÅŸÇÿ© ÿßŸÑŸÖŸÅÿ™ÿ±ÿ∂ÿ© ŸÅŸä ÿßŸÑÿπŸÑÿßŸÇÿßÿ™ ÿßŸÑÿ≤Ÿàÿ¨Ÿäÿ©

ŸÅŸä ÿ•ÿ∑ÿßÿ± ÿ≠ŸÖŸÑÿ© ÿßŸÑŸÄ 16 ŸäŸàŸÖ ŸÑŸÖŸÜÿßŸáÿ∂ÿ© ÿßŸÑÿπŸÜŸÅ ÿ∂ÿØ ÿßŸÑŸÖÿ±ÿ£ÿ©ÿå ÿ™ŸÇŸàŸÖ ÿÆÿ±Ÿäÿ∑ÿ© ÿßŸÑÿ™ÿ≠ÿ±ÿ¥ ŸàŸÖÿ¥ÿ±Ÿàÿπ ÿ®ÿµŸâ ÿ®ÿ≠ŸÖŸÑÿ© ŸÖÿ¥ÿ™ÿ±ŸÉÿ© ÿπŸÜ ÿßŸÑŸÖŸàÿßŸÅŸÇÿ© ŸÅŸä ÿßŸÑÿπŸÑÿßŸÇÿßÿ™ Ÿàÿ£ŸáŸÖŸäÿ™Ÿáÿß ŸÅŸä ÿ™ÿ≠ÿØŸäÿØ ÿßŸÑÿ£ŸÅÿπÿßŸÑ ÿßŸÑÿ™Ÿä ÿ™ÿπÿ™ÿ®ÿ± ÿ™ÿ≠ÿ±ÿ¥ ÿ£Ÿà ÿπŸÜŸÅ ÿ¨ŸÜÿ≥Ÿä
 ÿ™ŸÇŸàŸÖ ÿ®ÿµŸâ ÿÆŸÑÿßŸÑ ÿ¥Ÿáÿ± ŸÜŸàŸÅŸÖÿ®ÿ± ŸàÿØŸäÿ≥ŸÖÿ®ÿ± ÿ®ŸÜÿ¥ÿ± ŸÇÿµÿµ ŸÖŸÜ ÿ≥ŸäÿØÿßÿ™ Ÿàÿ±ÿ¨ÿßŸÑ ÿπŸÜ ÿ™ÿ¨ÿßÿ±ÿ® ÿ™ÿπÿ±ÿ∂Ÿàÿß ŸÑŸáÿß ŸÅŸä ÿπŸÑÿßŸÇÿßÿ™ŸáŸÖ ÿßŸÑÿ¥ÿÆÿµŸäÿ© ŸÖÿπ ÿ¢ÿÆÿ±ŸäŸÜ ÿ®ÿØŸàŸÜ ŸÖŸàÿßŸÅŸÇÿ™ŸáŸÖ

ŸÑŸÖÿ¥ÿßÿ±ŸÉÿ© ÿßŸÑŸÇÿµÿµ ÿ®ÿ±ÿ¨ÿßÿ° ŸÖŸÑÿ° ÿßŸÑÿßÿ≥ÿ™ŸÖÿßÿ±ÿ©: https://goo.gl/forms/daazuqogqqgarexg3

ŸÑŸÖÿ™ÿßÿ®ÿπÿ© ÿßŸÑÿ≠ŸÖŸÑÿ© ÿπŸÑŸä @harassmap  #ÿ®ÿπÿØ_ÿ•ÿ∞ŸÜŸä #ÿ®ÿµŸâ #ÿÆÿ±Ÿäÿ∑ÿ©_ÿßŸÑÿ™ÿ≠ÿ±ÿ¥ #16_ŸäŸàŸÖ #ÿßŸÑÿ™ÿ≠ÿ±ÿ¥_ŸÅŸä_ÿßŸÑÿ¥ÿßÿ±ÿπ

ask first ‚Äúit‚Äôs impolite to say no. go sit on your uncle‚Äôs lap and give him a kiss!‚Äù
‚Äúi don‚Äôt remember saying yes. i don‚Äôt remember saying no. i don‚Äôt remember being asked at all‚Äù
‚Äúyou probably implied that you wanted it. why would he even ask you when you look like someone who‚Äôd want it?‚Äô from an unwanted handshake or hug‚Äîeven from the people closest to us‚Äîto the so-called ‚Äúimplied consent‚Äù in marital sexual intercourse, we‚Äôre often put in situations that happen without our consent 
the bussy project and harassmap are launching a joint campaign within the framework of the ‚Äú16 days of activism to end violence against women‚Äù campaign about consent in relationships and its importance in defining what constitutes sexual harassment and sexual violence

to share your story please use our anonymous form: https://goo.gl/forms/daazuqogqqgarexg3

to follow the campaign, please check out @harassmap

#askfirst #bussy #harassmap #gendertech #16days #metoo #storytelling #endsh #orangetheworld

text:
*women rights*

human rights are women rights and women rights are human rights. let's end violence against women and girls! 
_
25 november is the international day to end violence against women. unfortunately, women do still have to fight for their rights and security every day, everywhere on this planet. we need effective political decisions and actions to end this!
_
saturday 24 november was a great day in france. tens of thousands of people were united in the streets to protest violence against women. demonstrations drew around 50000 according to organizer #noustoutes. it was a fantastic feminist tidal wave against gender violence. we are waiting for powerful political actions now. 
_
there were also many other womens' protests in europe, like in rome, geneva, athens or madrid. let's be united in europe and the world! #sorority #sororit√©

you can join nous toutes movement here: @noustoutes2411 + noustoutes.org
_
and let's join the un #16days of activism against gender-based violence campaign, because it is really time to end all kinds of violence against women and girls everywhere in the world! #orangetheworld 
the campaign starts today, the international day for the elimination of violence against women, and ends 10 december, human rights day. @unwomen
more information:
http://www.unwomen.org/en/what-we-do/ending-violence-against-women/take-action/16-days-of-activism
#hearmetoo
_

text:
understanding rape culture 101

in a recent¬†poll¬†by¬†thomas reuters foundation, india was ranked as the least safe country in the world for women, discerned as having the worst record of rapes, sexual harassment and violence against women.

this poll might be hard to believe for many indians, but the truth is that we live in a culture that normalises rape, violence and harassment against women. rape culture refers to the tendency of seeing violence and misogyny as an expression or part of ‚Äòtradition‚Äô or ‚Äòculture‚Äô and begins with our everyday use of sexist language and glorification of sexual violence in popular culture.

degradation of women, evident through numerous incidents such as eve-teasing (street sexual harassment), groping, flashing, revenge porn, stalking, among others, is a consequence of day-to-day normalised sexist behaviour. they are a result of certain actions and beliefs that normalise rape.

violence against women does not take place in isolation; it is a part of systematic rape culture. it starts with normalisation of rape and sexual assaults, leading to degradation of women, which finally perpetuates into more violent and sexual assaults. actions and attitudes we term as ‚Äòharmless‚Äô and ‚Äònot related to rape‚Äô are in fact part of this structure and reinforce, as well as excuse, more violent sexual acts.
.
.

repost @the_art_tiffin .
chains and boundaries. [trigger warning] ‚ñ™Ô∏è
today is international day of elimination of violence against women, and it is harrowing to read the statistics. at least  100 uk women killed by men or where a man is the principal suspect by 24 september this year 100 women in 267 days is one woman dead every 2.6 days.  over 20% of women in england and wales have suffered some form of sexual violence since the age of 16. considering rape or attempted rape alone it is 5.5% and 0.3%. these are shocking statistics, and yet we hear more in uk media about immigration and about terrorism.
.
‚ñ™Ô∏è
so many women do not come forwards. so many women come forwards but are not believed. and so many women are made to feel ashamed by questions such as ‚Äòso why did you stay?‚Äô dv and abuse takes different forms and coercive control is one of them, which is not so easy to prove and not easy to escape from. abuse of any form breaks down the spirit and self-worth and self-esteem something which prevents so many women leaving until it is too late. we need to have more stringent legal systems in place, and we have to believe women. let us end of culture of silence and let us put survivors at the centre of any action @unwomen we have to enable more women to share their stories without shame and stigma, and we have to consider the multi-faceted nature of abuse and violence. and for any man who says ‚Äòwhat about men‚Äô, honestly do have a considered look at your unconscious biases, and instead think of what you can do to help this. ‚ñ™Ô∏è .

text:
after this woman survived a homophobic and misogynist attack, her assailants were let free while she was arrested. alongside ni una menos, she is advocating for her record to be wiped and for justice to be done. 
despite a 2012 law which raised the maximum prison sentence for ‚Äúfemicide,‚Äù the killing of a woman or girl on account of her gender, argentina is still struggling against widespread gender-based violence. thankfully, a grassroots, women-led movement known as ni una menos (not one [woman] less) has arisen in argentina, and is working to empower women and defend their human rights. in this series, karl mancini (@karlitomancini) shares some of his work on the inspiring women of ni una menos and their fight for justice. to learn more about both mancini's work and ni una menos, please follow the link in our bio. 
#opensociety #argentina #niunamenos #femicide #femicidio #conmisderechosnotemetas #16days #genderbasedviolence #metoo #hearmetoo #homophobia

text:
kikelomo woleosho's boy project.
 i have spent 85% of my advocacy talking to girls and women. now my team and i have decided to take boys more seriously. we want to influence and positively affect our boys and men.

i have a 14 yr old brother and i want him to view life and women from a beautiful perspective. beyond my brother, i want to reach out to his male friends, his male neighbors and other boys in our community, nigeria and africa.

our first boy project is going to be a lunch meeting for boys in the underserved community of agbado. 
it will be a 2hours 30mins meeting with a distinguished man who is living purpose and is willing to impact the next male generation.

we hope this experience serves as a memorial for the boys to aim at achieving the future that will change africa.

like i always say together we can change our community a person at a time.

#boysproject #boys #boysempowerment
#kikelomowoleosho #kikelomoboaz #boysprojectbykikelomo #communitydevelopment #mentoring #hearmetoo #metoo #notoviolence #chnageinafrica #africa #mondaymotivation

text:
thanks to aisling from #dorset for this beautiful portrait of gaia, calling for justice for her. #artforgaia a project that hopes to bring together contributions from artists, the public and survivors, in memory of gaia pope & to highlight injustice around sexual violence, mental health and inequality. 
gaia was an artist and a survivor of sexual violence who struggled with #ptsd in the lead up to her disappearance and death in november 2018 when she was just 19 years old. what happened to gaia has become a national story and her family, who lead the @justiceforgaia campaign, want to use this platform to highlight the challenges faced by her and so many others. 
the art for gaia project, which is being followed by bbc news, is one way the campaign seeks to raise awareness and create a space where people can be heard, the way gaia deserved to be heard. 
to find out more, click the website link on our profile.

text:
i‚Äôll never forget this conversation. things got real dramatic between me and the narcissist around the 4th month mark. random people were contacting me to warn me about him, i was watching him lie to his friends, i saw his temper, i saw his alcoholism, and i didn‚Äôt like how he was speaking to me at times. but i kept focusing on the amazing, flawless first 3 months of our relationship. surely, we could get back to being those head-over-heels soulmates.
.
then my friend, who had been married for a number of years at the time, reminded me this was the beginning of our relationship. if things were this dramatic and making me unhappy at four months, it was only going to get worse. and she was right. it never got better, it only got worse.
.

text:
üçÇorange the worldüçÇ

according to  unwomen.org one in three women worldwide experience gender-based violence.

ever since i was a teenager or even younger i've been told to always carry somesort of defensespray with me and to hold  keys in my hand, when walking somewhere alone, in order to defend myself in case of an asult.  sometimes the advice, even from police have been to not walk alone at all.

unfortunately time showed that mayby i should have listened to these advices.

i wanna hold hands, carry flowers and puppies not be armoured, carrying weapons and i wanna be able to walk the earth al(l)one.

i am convinced that most people of all genders are kind and loving yet violence, abuse, sexualharassment and one in three women worldwide experience gender-based violence are undeniable facts.

it is time to change, an other world is possible. 
orange the world and #hearmetoo

peace and love .
.
.
